{
  "stem": "11552.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Kathy, I want to share two things with you which are very important.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There weren't too many people who escaped from graves.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You must be wondering, how come all these thousands of people were piled around?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "True, we were surrounded there, that we didn't run, that we didn't do something.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now remember, among us, maybe half and maybe less were children-- were infants.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If people started running, these children would suffer a terrible death.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, this is why we did not run, and this is why we remained very quiet.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I want to tell you in front of me was standing a father with a boy about 10 years old.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the boy turned to the father and asked him in Yiddish, father, will it hurt?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the father said, no, child.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when they shot them, the father was still embracing his son, and the son fell into the grave alive.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You saw this?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I heard them and I understood the Yiddish because he asked-- if it [NON-ENGLISH], and I don't know-- didn't know too much Yiddish, but I understood that.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the second thing I want to tell you, which is extremely important--",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What happened, but I just want to bring up another point.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At this grave in Kopyczynce, in the beginning of the summer of 1943 when the ghetto was being canceled, I want to bear witness to this, that at the grave were not only the SS men, but they were the Wehrmacht, ordinary soldiers, and the Luftwaffe pilots were there, killing us.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because in history, they believed that it was just Nazis-- they called them Nazis.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And not only were they killing us, but they were throwing the babies, and they were shooting, and they were hilarious.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I saw it with my own eyes.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
